{
  "name": "JARVIC-007 \u2014 Intelligence Core",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "sticky-intro",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        160,
        80
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## \ud83d\udd76\ufe0f JARVIC-007 \u2014 Intelligence Core\n\n**Setup checklist:**\n1. Set `YOUR_PHONE_NUMBER` in the Identity Check node (international format, no +)\n2. Add `Anthropic API` credential (HTTP Header Auth, name: `x-api-key`)\n3. Add `WhatsApp Business Cloud` credential (Bearer token from Meta)\n4. Add `Google Calendar OAuth2` credential\n5. Set your `PHONE_NUMBER_ID` from Meta Business in the WhatsApp send nodes\n6. Set your `CALENDAR_ID` in the Google Calendar nodes\n7. Activate the workflow\n\n**Webhook URL:** copy from the WhatsApp Incoming node \u2192 use in Meta App Dashboard \u2192 Webhooks",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 480,
        "color": 7
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "wh1",
      "name": "\ud83d\udcf1 WhatsApp Incoming",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.webhook",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        700,
        300
      ],
      "webhookId": "jarvis-007",
      "parameters": {
        "httpMethod": "POST",
        "path": "jarvis-007",
        "responseMode": "lastNode",
        "options": {}
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "code-extract",
      "name": "\ud83d\udd0d Extract Message",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        920,
        300
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const body = $input.first().json;\n\n// Handle Meta webhook verification challenge\nif (body['hub.challenge']) {\n  return [{ json: { challenge: body['hub.challenge'], isVerification: true } }];\n}\n\nconst entry = body?.entry?.[0];\nconst change = entry?.changes?.[0];\nconst value = change?.value;\nconst message = value?.messages?.[0];\n\nif (!message) return []; // Not a message, skip\n\nconst text = message.text?.body\n  || message.interactive?.button_reply?.title\n  || message.interactive?.list_reply?.title\n  || '';\n\nif (!text) return []; // No text content\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    messageId: message.id,\n    from: message.from,\n    text: text.trim(),\n    timestamp: message.timestamp,\n    phoneNumberId: value?.metadata?.phone_number_id || 'PHONE_NUMBER_ID',\n    senderName: value?.contacts?.[0]?.profile?.name || 'Commander',\n    isVerification: false\n  }\n}];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "if-identity",
      "name": "\ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Commander Identity Check",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1140,
        300
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "options": {
            "caseSensitive": false,
            "leftValue": "",
            "typeValidation": "loose"
          },
          "combinator": "and",
          "conditions": [
            {
              "id": "id-cond",
              "leftValue": "={{ $json.from }}",
              "rightValue": "YOUR_PHONE_NUMBER",
              "operator": {
                "type": "string",
                "operation": "equals",
                "name": "filter.operator.equals"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "http-claude-brain",
      "name": "\ud83e\udd16 JARVIC Brain (Claude)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [
        1360,
        200
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "httpHeaderAuth": {
          "id": "anthropic-api",
          "name": "Anthropic API Key"
        }
      },
      "parameters": {
        "method": "POST",
        "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages",
        "sendHeaders": true,
        "headerParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            {
              "name": "anthropic-version",
              "value": "2023-06-01"
            },
            {
              "name": "x-api-key",
              "value": "={{ $credentials.httpHeaderAuth.value }}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "sendBody": true,
        "specifyBody": "json",
        "jsonBody": "={\n  \"model\": \"claude-opus-4-5\",\n  \"max_tokens\": 1024,\n  \"messages\": [\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"You are JARVIC-007 \u2014 a suave, razor-sharp AI intelligence officer and personal butler hybrid. Think Jarvis from Iron Man meets Q from James Bond. You live in WhatsApp as your Commander's right hand.\\n\\nAnalyze this incoming transmission from your Commander and extract:\\n1. MISSION_TYPE: schedule | reschedule | cancel | message_someone | find_service | briefing | unclear\\n2. INTEL: {\\n     \\\"personnel\\\": [],\\n     \\\"date_preference\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n     \\\"time_preference\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n     \\\"duration\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n     \\\"location\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n     \\\"budget\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n     \\\"special_notes\\\": \\\"\\\",\\n     \\\"priority_level\\\": \\\"routine\\\"\\n   }\\n3. JARVIC_RESPONSE: A short, sophisticated acknowledgment in character (dry British wit, calm competence, subtle Bond references). Max 2 sentences.\\n\\nIncoming Transmission: \\\"{{ $json.text }}\\\"\\n\\nRespond in JSON only. No markdown, no code blocks, raw JSON.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
        "options": {}
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "http-unauthorized",
      "name": "\ud83d\udeab Ignore Unauthorized",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.noOp",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1360,
        420
      ],
      "parameters": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "code-parse",
      "name": "\ud83d\udccb Parse Mission Brief",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        1580,
        200
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const response = $input.first().json;\nconst raw = response.content?.[0]?.text || '{}';\n\nlet parsed;\ntry {\n  const clean = raw.replace(/```json\\n?|```/g, '').trim();\n  parsed = JSON.parse(clean);\n} catch(e) {\n  parsed = {\n    MISSION_TYPE: 'unclear',\n    INTEL: {},\n    JARVIC_RESPONSE: \"I beg your pardon, Commander. Could you rephrase that mission brief? I want to make sure I execute it flawlessly.\"\n  };\n}\n\nconst extract = $('\ud83d\udd0d Extract Message').first().json;\n\nreturn [{\n  json: {\n    MISSION_TYPE: (parsed.MISSION_TYPE || 'unclear').toLowerCase(),\n    INTEL: parsed.INTEL || {},\n    JARVIC_RESPONSE: parsed.JARVIC_RESPONSE || '',\n    from: extract.from,\n    phoneNumberId: extract.phoneNumberId,\n    senderName: extract.senderName,\n    originalText: extract.text\n  }\n}];"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "switch-router",
      "name": "\ud83d\udd00 Mission Router",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.switch",
      "typeVersion": 3,
      "position": [
        1800,
        200
      ],
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "rules",
        "rules": {
          "values": [
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": false,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "loose"
                },
                "combinator": "and",
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.MISSION_TYPE }}",
                    "rightValue": "schedule",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals",
                      "name": "filter.operator.equals"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "outputKey": "SCHEDULE"
            },
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": false,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "loose"
                },
                "combinator": "and",
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.MISSION_TYPE }}",
                    "rightValue": "reschedule",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals",
                      "name": "filter.operator.equals"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "outputKey": "RESCHEDULE"
            },
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": false,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "loose"
                },
                "combinator": "and",
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.MISSION_TYPE }}",
                    "rightValue": "message_someone",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals",
                      "name": "filter.operator.equals"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "outputKey": "MESSAGE"
            },
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": false,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "loose"
                },
                "combinator": "and",
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.MISSION_TYPE }}",
                    "rightValue": "find_service",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals",
                      "name": "filter.operator.equals"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "outputKey": "FIND"
            },
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": false,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "loose"
                },
                "combinator": "and",
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.MISSION_TYPE }}",
                    "rightValue": "briefing",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals",
                      "name": "filter.operator.equals"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "outputKey": "BRIEFING"
            }
          ]
        },
        "fallbackOutput": "extra"
      }
    },
    {
